<main>
  <h1><%= race.name %></h1>
  <p>
    Before the days of men and elves and dwarves, the land was ruled by Bahamut the Brilliant. He reigned for untold millennia, until a battle
    between he and his sister Tiamat resulted in their deaths, and the end of the dragons. Though, the death of the wyrms birthed a new people.
    Though not as large and powerful, the dragonborn are now the closest thing most will see to a dragon.
  </p>

  <h2>Visage of the Drakes</h2>
  <p>
    Towering and imposing in frame, and brightly colored in magnificent scales, the dragonborn are not difficult to notice. Though they lack wings
    and tails, they inherited the dragons' claws and fangs, as well as the power of the breath weapon.
  </p>

  <h2>Dark and Twisted Sorcery</h2>
  <p>
    Legends say a shaman from an early human tribe discovered an ancient ritual, lost to time. Using the blood of the newly dead dragons, he
    transformed his followers into the first dragonborn. They gained great power and took on the aspect of the dragon, at the cost of their
    lifespan. Some tellings suggest the shaman went on an expedition into the Wound, to uncover the blood of Bahamut and Tiamat.
  </p>

  <h2><%= race.name %> Traits</h2>
  <p>The dormant power of the dragons' blood grants dragonborn a number of inherent draconic abilities.</p>
  <%- include("race") %>

  <% race = raceMain.sub[0] %>
  <h3><%= race.name %></h3>
  <p>
    These dragonborn are descended from the chromatic dragons who rose up against their metallic fathers, leading to the war that sparked the
    downfall of dragonkind. Lesser in power but greater in number, their immunity to dragon breath attacks made them adept kinslayers, and their
    might and number drove even the proud dwarves to hide under the earth.
  </p>
  <p>
    Though they are the most common type of dragonborn, they can't quite escape the shadow of their malevolent forebears. Their scales are
    colorful but dull, lacking the vibrance of the true dragons.
  </p>
