    old were not as plentiful as their chromatic children, dragonborn of this type are rare, though still far more common than gem dragons.
  </p>
  <p>
    Their bodies are coated in scales of metal, but are rough and dull, a pale reflection of Bahamut's brilliance. Some see them as living symbols
    of good, remnants of a bygone era when law and virtue ruled, though since no living creature can remember that age, these views are highly
    romanticized.
  </p>
